<li id="cite_note-27"><b><a href="#cite_ref-27" title="">^</a></b> Soda-lime glass for containers is slightly different from soda-lime glass for windows (also called flat glass or <a href="/wiki/Float_glass" title="Float glass">float glass</a>). Float glass has a higher <a href="/wiki/Magnesium_oxide" title="Magnesium oxide">magnesium oxide</a> content as compared to container glass, and a lower silica and <a href="/wiki/Calcium_oxide" title="Calcium oxide">calcium oxide</a> content. For further details see main article <a href="/wiki/Soda-lime_glass" title="Soda-lime glass">Soda-lime glass</a>.</li>
